1
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:53,120
<i>Where's my blue bag?</i>

2
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:02,280
<i>I don't care. No.</i>

3
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:17,080
<i>- Pim, do you have him?
- I got him.</i>

4
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:18,760
<i>He's leaving the house.</i>

5
00:01:18,960 --> 00:01:20,840
<i>He's late today.</i>

6
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:32,040
<i>- Where are you? Are you right there?
- No, I'm across the street.</i>

7
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,320
<i>- Get closer than that.
- I'm not gonna lose him.</i>

8
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:45,880
<i>- I'm not gonna lose him.
- Pay attention, guys.</i>

9
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:55,120
<i>9:01, down Granville Park. Again.</i>

10
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:00,240
<i>Okay, switch to channel seven.</i>

11
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,080
<i>Sarah!</i>

12
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,640
<i>Hi.</i>

13
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,200
<i>Control the flow of traffic.</i>

14
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:43,480
<i>Come on! Come here, Rusty!</i>

15
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:53,080
<i>Rusty. Rusty, come here.</i>

16
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,600
<i>Come... Rusty!</i>

17
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,840
<i>Come on, boy.</i>

18
00:02:58,440 --> 00:03:00,160
<i>Come on. We're gonna be late.</i>

19
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,840
<i>Hello, Jack.</i>

20
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:07,360
<i>- Sarah, could you turn it down, please?
- What?</i>

21
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:10,520
<i>The music, if that's what it is.
Turn it down.</i>

22
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:12,640
<i>- Why?
- Has anyone let the dog out yet?</i>

23
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:16,640
<i>- It's Sarah's turn! I did it last time!
- It takes, what, two seconds?</i>

24
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,840
Rusty, no! Leave it alone!

25
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,640
Come on!

26
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,440
<i>Andy, stop it.</i>

27
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:27,920
Andy! Mom, tell Andy to get that thing
out of here. It's screwing up the TV.

28
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,960
Idiot.

29
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:32,760
Andy, a little help here, okay?

30
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:35,040
- Moron.
- Idiot moron.

31
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,480
- Moron idiot.
- Nobody's an idiot.

32
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,760
- Except for her.
- Nobody's a moron.

33
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:43,040
- Except for her.
- Andy, stop it!

34
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,480
I'm trying to watch this.

35
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:47,680
Those two home together all week?

36
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:51,440
- There's no school till Monday.
- Oh, boy. What's your day like?

37
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:55,160
Finish the details on the Morgan house.
They're pouring the footings today.

38
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:59,160
Then I have to find a guitar teacher
for Sarah, pay some bills...

39
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,720
...and schlepping the kids.

40
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:04,640
You should get yourself a hobby,
keep yourself busy.

41
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,960
- I already have a hobby.
- Yeah?

42
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:09,760
And it's taking care of you.

43
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,880
I don't deserve you.

44
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,320
No, you don't.

45
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:16,280
We owe Arlin and Vee a dinner.
Wanna do it this week?

46
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:19,640
Well, they're home this week.
I just wanna be with the kids.

47
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:23,880
- Mom! Tell Andy to get that thing out!
- Really?

48
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:27,720
You should have Marci drop
my blue suit off at the cleaners.

49
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:29,920
Marci's in Manila till the 26th.

50
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,960
Here, sport, give me this for a second.

51
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:37,160
- Mom! Excuse me, does anybody care?
- This is what's doing it.

52
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:40,160
Put this in my office.
I'll show you how we can fix it.

53
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:43,560
Okay? And, yes, I do care.

54
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:48,040
- Goodbye.
- Bye, Jack.

55
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:50,280
- Bye, Dad.
- Bye, Andy.

56
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:53,560
Don't torture your sister.

57
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:58,640
Sarah, this dog needs to go out.
Don't forget his new collar.

58
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,480
- Sarah.
- Bye, Jack.

59
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:11,240
<i>Getting a welcome break in the weather
before getting hit by a couple of storms.</i>

60
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:13,440
<i>That'll make the drive more difficult.</i>

61
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:17,080
<i>Looks like smooth sailing this morning
heading into downtown Seattle.</i>

62
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:21,960
<i>We've been seeing slowdowns and
heavy traffic just about everywhere else...</i>

63
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:49,240
- Morning.
- Morning, Richard.

64
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:52,920
- Morning, Cindy. How are you?
- Morning, Jack. Great, thanks.

65
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,960
How do I say this, Bobby?

66
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:58,680
- No.
- Come on, Janet. I don't see why not.

67
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:02,080
Look, Bobby, here's how this works.
You ask me out, which you did.

68
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,720
I say no, which I did.

69
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:07,040
You say, "Okay," and ask somebody else.
You don't keep asking me.

70
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,360
At what point does it become
sexual harassment?

71
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,800
Right about now, Bobby.

72
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,880
- Mr. Stanfield.
- Morning, boss.

73
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,080
- Kid's persistent.
- I don't know why.

74
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:18,920
- The usual reason, I suppose.
- Have you seen Ravi yet?

75
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,880
No, I'm on my way now, though.

76
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,600
Don't forget, merger meeting.

77
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,760
- Nice flowers.
- Born-again Bobby.

78
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:30,600
- Maybe he's trying to save your soul.
- He'd need bigger blossoms than that.

79
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,680
- Good morning, Betty.
- Morning.

80
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:46,360
- How we doing?
- Pike Street system's running slow.

81
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:49,360
I'll tell Carol when she gets in.
We'll get after it.

82
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:52,680
Merger goes through, we'll go in
and replace the whole thing.

83
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:54,320
Yeah.

84
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:58,240
- Morning, sir.
- Good morning, Rick.

85
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,640
Hey, Ravi. What have we got?

86
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,240
Brute-force login.
The interesting thing is...

87
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,080
...he's coming in through Hong Kong,
Korea and Malaysia...

88
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:11,480
...but he's trying sequential account
numbers. He's hacking all over.

89
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,320
Move over for me.

90
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:19,160
Let's try a rule change on him,
see what he does.

91
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:22,840
Put in an IPS signature
that black-holes the pattern.

92
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:27,520
- See if that slows him down.
- That'd slow me down.

93
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:31,000
- That'd be resistant to false positives too.
- Yep.

94
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,840
Thanks.

95
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:37,840
Loss is higher than one would expect,
considering your level of security.

96
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,480
Just write it off?

97
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:41,680
That depends on how
you view the statistics.

98
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:45,120
They're not particularly high,
given the fact that...

99
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:49,680
...we're pushing the business into
some new and uncharted areas.

100
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:52,320
Online banking is where
the business is heading.

101
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,800
Where we have our branches...

102
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,560
...we'll provide our customers with
more ways to control their money.

103
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,920
As you can see by the chart,
after the merger...

104
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:02,800
...Accuwest will have 1100 branches
in 13 states...

105
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:06,360
...with over 100 billion in assets.
So to answer you, Harry, yes...

106
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:11,480
...we do see a reasonable level of fraud
loss as a cost of doing business.

107
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:14,400
- How many branches do you have?
- Twenty-seven.

108
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:16,960
As head of network security, Jack...

109
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:20,480
...you've never really had to think
in terms of economies of scale.

110
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:24,760
- But your philosophy of risk is...
- Wait a second, Gary.

111
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:29,440
Make this clear for me, will you?
What exactly is my philosophy of risk?

112
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:32,800
- No need to take this personally.
- I take it personally, goddamn it.

113
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:36,400
I've spent 20 years protecting this bank,
its customers and shareholders...

114
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,040
...from unnecessary risk.

115
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:41,480
Jack, I don't think you're hearing
what I'm saying.

116
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:44,280
I hear what you're saying.
Fraud loss is inevitable...

117
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:47,920
...pass it on to the customers
as the cost of doing business.

118
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,720
We don't wanna do that, do we?

119
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,960
We're all here to serve the customers.
Let's try and get along.

120
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:58,760
- We can have the best of both worlds.
- Doesn't exist, Arlin.

121
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:03,120
Look, I'm sorry. This went on
a little longer than I anticipated.

122
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:06,120
There's stuff I really have to get to.

123
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:11,640
- Okay, let's get on with it.
- Network attacks...

124
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:13,800
...network activity.

125
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:19,600
- Where is this guy?
- He's in reception.

126
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:22,080
He said it's personal. Should I get him?

127
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:24,120
No, I'll walk over there.

128
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:30,920
Mr. Stanfield, Mr. Hughes.

129
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,960
Jack Stanfield, Mr. Hughes.

130
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,760
- Do I know you?
- I know you.

131
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,840
- Do you have a card?
- Oh, yeah.

132
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,280
DHD Financial. What can I do for you?

133
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,320
You can give me
the $95,000 you owe me.

134
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,160
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- No?

135
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:53,080
I'm collecting for GambleNet U.S.A.
Does that ring a bell?

136
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:57,000
- No, it doesn't.
- You racked up 95 grand in online wagers.

137
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,600
And I got the paperwork to prove it.

138
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:02,160
You got the wrong Jack Stanfield.
I don't gamble.

139
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:06,120
- I don't have any debt. Check your facts.
- You're a deadbeat. See you in court.

140
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:08,960
- Laurie, call security.
- Don't bother, sweetheart.

141
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:13,440
Gambling's an addiction, Mr. Stanfield.
Get some help.

142
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,960
Well, I thought the idea was
to match it to the curtains.

143
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:37,760
- Yes, but if you do that...
- Nice flowers.

144
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,280
Bobby?

145
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:42,120
That would be the wrong thing to do,
don't you think?

146
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,200
- What's up, partner?
- Take a look at this.

147
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,400
Who were you betting on?

148
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,240
I wasn't betting. I don't gamble.

149
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:56,120
- I don't even know how.
- Well, that's obvious.

150
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:59,920
You think somebody got my information off
the bank's internal network or what?

151
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:02,080
Are you doubting yourself
in your old age?

152
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:04,840
No. More likely a dumpster diver...

153
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,600
- ... somebody sifting through your trash.
- Maybe.

154
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:11,520
A debt collector showed up
this morning about it.

155
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:13,400
Don't worry. I'll clean it up.

156
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:16,040
It's just a pain in the ass.

157
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,080
Bill Cox? Guy from Atlanta.

158
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,200
- Supposed to have a drink.
- I can do 5:30.

159
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,120
I wanna get home early, pizza night.

160
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:24,480
- Good. I'll let him know.
- Okay.

161
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,680
<i>- Hey, you.
- Hi, hon.</i>

162
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:35,080
<i>Harry and I need to see a guy
for a few minutes after work.</i>

163
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:37,280
<i>- Okay if I'm late?
- What are you thinking?</i>

164
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:40,280
<i>I don't know, 45 minutes, tops.</i>

165
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,680
We'll see you when we see you.
Love you.

166
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:45,040
<i>Love you too. Bye.</i>

167
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,840
I see him. My question is this:

168
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:56,960
Do we really wanna work
for those Accuwest morons?

169
00:11:57,120 --> 00:12:00,240
- I'll listen to what he has to say.
- This guy could be our future.

170
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,440
Okay, okay.

171
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,640
- Bill.
- Good to see you, Harry.

172
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,440
- Bill Cox, Jack Stanfield.
- How are you?

173
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:10,280
I've been looking forward to meeting you.
Please, sit.

174
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,880
Thank you.

175
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:23,400
Sarah, the pizza's here.
My wallet's by the door.

176
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:31,040
Is somebody gonna get that?

177
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:35,560
- Here you go.
- So listen...

178
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:38,880
...I don't know how much Harry's told you
about what I do.

179
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:42,400
Not a lot. Just that you're in banking.

180
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:45,520
I have a company that provides
banking-support services...

181
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:49,000
...mainly in the South, but, really,
I'm an old-fashioned entrepreneur.

182
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:56,040
If that's a scary movie, turn it off.
Your brother won't sleep for a week.

183
00:12:58,160 --> 00:13:00,400
- I'm so sorry to make you...
- Hello.

184
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:05,880
- Sarah!
- Mom.

185
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:07,120
Call 911!

186
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:10,120
There's over 200 regional banks
in the U.S. Alone...

187
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:14,720
...that have nothing like the sophistication
of the system you developed for Landrock.

188
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:18,080
Sarah! Leave her alone!

189
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:21,520
With your system's software...

190
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:24,840
...Harry's expertise in law enforcement
and the physical security...

191
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,520
...you're an unbeatable team.

192
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,000
Hey! Come here!

193
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:30,360
No!

194
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:33,360
- What are you doing to me? Get away!
- Shut up!

195
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,160
You'd be your own bosses.

196
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,480
I'd just supply the money.

197
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:41,040
- Don't hurt my children.
- Shut up!

198
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:43,480
Oh, my God, what do you want?

199
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:46,080
I have to think about
a couple of other options...

200
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,360
...but this sounds very attractive.

201
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,800
Okay, good.

202
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,720
I hate to break this up.

203
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:55,520
- I gotta get home.
- Family man.

204
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:58,560
No! Daddy!

205
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,240
So how many kids do you have?

206
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:05,680
Two. Boy, 8. Girl, 14.

207
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:08,640
- Sure you don't need a ride?
- No, thanks, Harry. I'm fine.

208
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,080
Going back tonight?

209
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:15,880
- No, I've got some business here in town.
- Well, great meeting you. Take care.

210
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,120
She has beautiful eyes, your daughter.

211
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:35,480
What?

212
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,320
Jesus, what..?

213
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,600
Oh, my God. What do you want?

214
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,640
I wanna get you home. It's pizza night.

215
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:48,320
Drive.

216
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:50,680
Drive.

217
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:11,160
Liam, we're on our way.
Everything all right?

218
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:15,320
Fine, the house is secure.
And we're setting up now.

219
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:17,840
I wanna talk to my wife.

220
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:20,360
You hear that, Liam?
He wants to talk to his wife.

221
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,480
They can't talk right now.

222
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,280
She's busy.

223
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,720
Who are you?

224
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:03,680
What's this about?

225
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,520
What do you want from me?

226
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,520
This is your exit, Jack.

227
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:08,000
<i>Three defenders had the chance
to put him on the ground.</i>

228
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,520
They're here.

229
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:13,280
<i>As good as he's been down the years.
Tremendous effort to stay alive.</i>

230
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,320
- Where are they?
- Through here.

231
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:42,120
Jesus.

232
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,440
- What is this?
- Daddy.

233
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:47,080
Why have you done this, for God's sake?

234
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:50,160
It's okay. They're children!

235
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,600
I said, "If they were trouble. "
Were they trouble?

