00:58:52,280 --> 00:58:54,960
Coming up. There you go.

740
00:58:55,800 --> 00:58:57,760
<i>Ready to run.</i>

741
00:58:57,920 --> 00:59:00,840
- I'm telling you, Arlin...
- Go and deal with it.

742
00:59:01,800 --> 00:59:03,240
It's running, Stacy.

743
00:59:03,400 --> 00:59:04,640
<i>Okay, if you need...</i>

744
00:59:04,840 --> 00:59:06,200
Go.

745
00:59:10,440 --> 00:59:12,200
With money moving every nanosecond...

746
00:59:12,360 --> 00:59:14,640
...we have to provide a platform
for technology...

747
00:59:14,840 --> 00:59:17,800
...to be able to maintain and control risk.

748
00:59:18,240 --> 00:59:22,120
- You have to be thinking outside the box.
- Oh, I understand.

749
00:59:22,280 --> 00:59:26,120
These geeks with their laptops can
figure out ways to steal money from you.

750
00:59:26,280 --> 00:59:28,720
- Arlin, you lost?
- Hi, Jack.

751
00:59:28,880 --> 00:59:32,360
No, Gary's trying to teach me something
about the new technology.

752
00:59:32,560 --> 00:59:33,760
- Well, good luck.
- Yeah.

753
00:59:33,960 --> 00:59:36,960
I told him you've been trying that
for years. What are you up to?

754
00:59:37,120 --> 00:59:38,760
Well, there's a...

755
00:59:38,920 --> 00:59:41,120
I came down because there was...

756
00:59:41,280 --> 00:59:43,400
...a maintenance issue
with one of the servers.

757
00:59:43,600 --> 00:59:45,280
Got the engineers coming down.

758
00:59:45,480 --> 00:59:48,080
I asked to be notified
about all maintenance issues.

759
00:59:48,280 --> 00:59:51,040
No one told me a server was down.

760
00:59:51,240 --> 00:59:54,760
They probably didn't realize the procedures
changed. Wichita didn't call you?

761
00:59:54,920 --> 00:59:56,400
No.

762
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:58,520
Who's "they"?

763
00:59:58,920 --> 01:00:01,320
I don't know. Janet took the call.

764
01:00:01,480 --> 01:00:03,440
Did you fire her this morning?

765
01:00:03,600 --> 01:00:05,720
You know, Arlin,
it just wasn't working out.

766
01:00:05,920 --> 01:00:07,960
Seems kind of sudden.

767
01:00:09,440 --> 01:00:11,640
Well, actually, it's been...

768
01:00:13,480 --> 01:00:15,720
It's been building for a while.

769
01:00:15,880 --> 01:00:20,320
Well, care to join us?
Help Gary unlock my analog brain?

770
01:00:20,480 --> 01:00:23,240
I think I'd better get back to the office.

771
01:00:26,920 --> 01:00:28,880
I'll check with you later.

772
01:00:30,200 --> 01:00:33,000
All right, Arlin, you gotta
understand two things:

773
01:00:33,160 --> 01:00:36,640
- Number one, analog is for sissies.
- So I gathered.

774
01:01:26,280 --> 01:01:28,520
He didn't wash his hands.

775
01:01:28,680 --> 01:01:31,640
That's why you should never eat
peanuts off a bar.

776
01:01:34,920 --> 01:01:36,520
Let's go.

777
01:01:54,280 --> 01:01:56,440
Can I take his collar off?

778
01:01:57,040 --> 01:01:59,880
- No, honey. He needs that.
- Beth, come with me, please.

779
01:02:01,120 --> 01:02:03,200
- Where?
- Just downstairs.

780
01:02:03,360 --> 01:02:05,040
Mom.

781
01:02:05,200 --> 01:02:07,560
- It's okay. I'll be right back.
- Now, Beth.

782
01:02:09,720 --> 01:02:10,920
Why do you hate us so much?

783
01:02:11,120 --> 01:02:15,240
I don't hate you, Sarah.
I just don't care about you.

784
01:02:19,240 --> 01:02:21,640
I need you to make a call.

785
01:02:25,280 --> 01:02:28,360
Why..? Why would I say this?

786
01:02:30,720 --> 01:02:32,800
Make him believe you.

787
01:02:46,640 --> 01:02:48,920
Well, hopefully, that's the way...

788
01:02:57,760 --> 01:02:59,400
Which one is he?

789
01:03:00,320 --> 01:03:01,760
The kid in the blue shirt.

790
01:03:07,720 --> 01:03:09,440
Come here.

791
01:03:13,640 --> 01:03:15,680
Mr. Stanfield, sir?
Why did Janet get fired?

792
01:03:15,880 --> 01:03:18,560
- She didn't do anything.
- We know what you're up to, Bobby.

793
01:03:18,760 --> 01:03:20,440
What I'm up to?
What do you mean?

794
01:03:20,600 --> 01:03:23,880
You and Janet have made repeated
attempts to access secure information.

795
01:03:24,040 --> 01:03:25,360
No, that's ridiculous.

796
01:03:25,520 --> 01:03:28,280
She rolled over on you, Bobby.
She gave you up.

797
01:03:28,440 --> 01:03:29,960
What are you talking about, sir?

798
01:03:30,400 --> 01:03:33,280
Sit down. Sit down.

799
01:05:09,560 --> 01:05:12,240
We'll be in touch, Bobby.

800
01:05:12,440 --> 01:05:13,760
Hello?

801
01:05:16,840 --> 01:05:18,520
It's done.

802
01:05:18,680 --> 01:05:21,000
Vel, is the money there?

803
01:05:22,040 --> 01:05:23,360
Okay, good.

804
01:05:23,520 --> 01:05:27,120
I've done everything you want.
When do I get my family back?

805
01:05:27,320 --> 01:05:30,360
We have some tidying up to do.

806
01:05:48,120 --> 01:05:52,280
Sir, I just wanted to say, regardless
of what you may have heard...

807
01:05:57,120 --> 01:05:59,480
There are hidden cameras
in all the public areas...

808
01:05:59,640 --> 01:06:02,520
...and some of the more sensitive areas
on the secure floors.

809
01:06:02,720 --> 01:06:04,960
So you can see
the whole bank from here?

810
01:06:05,160 --> 01:06:07,240
These are archive files.

811
01:06:07,400 --> 01:06:09,360
Ninety-one cameras
running on 20 screens.

812
01:06:09,680 --> 01:06:12,200
Wow, I bet you don't watch much TV
when you get home.

813
01:06:12,400 --> 01:06:14,160
I don't even have one.

814
01:06:15,120 --> 01:06:16,800
- Sorry. Sorry.
- I got it.

815
01:06:38,160 --> 01:06:39,880
Okay.

816
01:06:41,240 --> 01:06:44,640
- At least it didn't end up in the keyboard.
- Right.

817
01:06:47,120 --> 01:06:50,600
We better get out of here before
we completely screw things up.

818
01:06:50,800 --> 01:06:52,440
- Thanks. Sorry.
- Thank you.

819
01:06:52,640 --> 01:06:54,480
All right.

820
01:07:04,800 --> 01:07:07,080
- Where's Jack Stanfield?
- He just left.

821
01:07:07,240 --> 01:07:10,080
- What was he doing in here?
- Making one hell of a mess.

822
01:07:10,240 --> 01:07:13,240
- What the hell?
- What's wrong?

823
01:07:15,000 --> 01:07:16,840
All the camera files have been deleted.

824
01:07:30,640 --> 01:07:32,760
- What is this?
- Just press "send. "

825
01:07:43,920 --> 01:07:47,000
Now there's no network,
no account details.

826
01:07:48,200 --> 01:07:51,160
No trace of the 100 million.
Can I have the disk, please?

827
01:07:52,600 --> 01:07:57,400
Vel has a real talent
for being destructive...

828
01:07:57,560 --> 01:07:59,280
...do you not think?

829
01:08:02,880 --> 01:08:05,120
See you at the house, Jack.

830
01:08:09,680 --> 01:08:12,960
Jack, what's going on?
What are you up to?

831
01:08:13,120 --> 01:08:15,800
- I haven't got time for this now.
- You're gonna make time.

832
01:08:15,960 --> 01:08:20,080
You'll stay here and explain what you were
doing in areas you're not supposed to be in.

833
01:08:20,240 --> 01:08:22,200
No, I'm not.

834
01:08:23,040 --> 01:08:25,760
- Mr. Stanfield, the network...
- Tell him.

835
01:08:25,960 --> 01:08:28,720
- What is it?
- The network just crashed.

836
01:08:28,880 --> 01:08:30,800
- The whole floor?
- No, the whole building.

837
01:08:39,080 --> 01:08:40,680
Stanfield!

838
01:08:47,200 --> 01:08:48,760
Jack! Stop right there!

839
01:08:48,920 --> 01:08:50,640
Jack!

840
01:08:58,400 --> 01:09:00,200
- Get out of the car!
- Are you nuts?

841
01:09:00,400 --> 01:09:01,880
- You're nuts!
- Get away.

842
01:09:02,040 --> 01:09:06,240
Security-camera files are missing,
the computers just crashed!

843
01:09:20,240 --> 01:09:21,560
Call the police.

844
01:09:21,720 --> 01:09:24,520
Security. We're in the garage,
get the police.

845
01:09:24,720 --> 01:09:25,680
Shit.

846
01:09:42,360 --> 01:09:44,360
Beth?

847
01:09:47,280 --> 01:09:49,040
Beth!

848
01:09:55,120 --> 01:09:57,000
Beth!

849
01:10:00,240 --> 01:10:01,960
Beth?

850
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:06,520
Oh, my God.

851
01:10:47,440 --> 01:10:49,840
Where are they? Where's my family?

852
01:10:51,760 --> 01:10:53,360
Yeah, we're leaving now.

853
01:10:53,520 --> 01:10:55,240
I'll meet you when I'm done.

854
01:10:55,960 --> 01:10:57,720
Yeah, will do.

855
01:10:58,120 --> 01:11:00,080
- Cox says goodbye.
- Are they alive?

856
01:11:00,280 --> 01:11:02,040
Just tell me that. Are they alive?

857
01:11:02,200 --> 01:11:04,680
- Come on, man, talk to me.
- We're leaving now, Jack.

858
01:11:04,840 --> 01:11:07,200
Why? Just kill me here.
Why should I make it easy?

859
01:11:07,360 --> 01:11:11,120
You still think there's a chance you might
be able to help them. Now, let's go.

860
01:12:10,120 --> 01:12:12,920
<i>Hi, it's Harry. Leave a message.</i>

861
01:12:13,760 --> 01:12:17,240
<i>Harry. Jesus, Harry, where are you?</i>

862
01:12:17,720 --> 01:12:21,360
I'm in trouble. I'm in real trouble.

863
01:12:21,560 --> 01:12:23,200
I need...

864
01:12:23,400 --> 01:12:24,800
I need to talk to you.

865
01:12:24,960 --> 01:12:26,840
Call me on my... No, you can't.

866
01:12:27,040 --> 01:12:28,680
You can't call me on my cell.

867
01:12:28,840 --> 01:12:30,800
They're listening.

868
01:12:31,280 --> 01:12:33,040
Shit.

869
01:12:55,280 --> 01:12:57,720
It's really coming down, huh?

870
01:13:01,160 --> 01:13:04,440
- What a night.
- Well, it is Seattle.

871
01:14:29,120 --> 01:14:32,720
<i>Harry. Jesus, Harry, where are you?</i>

872
01:14:32,920 --> 01:14:35,680
<i>I'm in trouble. I'm in real trouble.</i>

873
01:14:35,840 --> 01:14:37,240
<i>I need to talk to you.</i>

874
01:14:37,400 --> 01:14:40,600
<i>Call me on my... No, you can't.
You can't call me on my cell.</i>

875
01:14:42,440 --> 01:14:44,160
<i>They're listening. Shit.</i>

876
01:14:45,920 --> 01:14:49,080
<i>This is Dr. Hay's office confirming
your 8 a. m. Appointment Monday.</i>

877
01:14:49,280 --> 01:14:51,760
<i>So we'll see you then.
Thank you. Bye-bye.</i>

878
01:14:52,720 --> 01:14:55,840
<i>Harry, I did it. I finally left him.</i>

879
01:14:56,000 --> 01:14:58,480
<i>God, I love you so much.</i>

880
01:14:58,680 --> 01:15:04,200
<i>I'm afraid. Get out of there, okay?
Come as soon as you can.</i>

881
01:15:05,120 --> 01:15:07,360
<i>I love you.</i>

882
01:15:07,600 --> 01:15:09,520
<i>Harry, it's Eric at Redline.</i>

883
01:15:09,680 --> 01:15:13,920
<i>I found a guy who's selling those
Porsche 356 parts you...</i>

884
01:15:16,800 --> 01:15:18,480
Yeah, come on in.

885
01:15:18,680 --> 01:15:20,240
Thank you.

886
01:15:21,960 --> 01:15:23,880
Wow, quite a place.

887
01:15:24,280 --> 01:15:28,520
Yeah. I wanted something sort of
Dean Martin-ish, you know what I mean?

888
01:15:29,000 --> 01:15:30,240
Well, you nailed it.

889
01:15:30,400 --> 01:15:31,880
You know, I had my doubts.

890
01:15:32,080 --> 01:15:33,360
But after our meeting...

891
01:15:33,560 --> 01:15:36,680
...I could tell Jack was
definitely interested.

892
01:15:36,920 --> 01:15:38,440
And the timing was perfect.

893
01:15:38,600 --> 01:15:41,920
Without the merger, Jack would
never consider leaving the bank...

894
01:15:42,080 --> 01:15:44,040
...and starting up on his own.

895
01:15:44,200 --> 01:15:46,160
- How about a beer?
- No, I'm good, thanks.

896
01:15:46,320 --> 01:15:50,240
Once Jack gets his teeth into it,
there'll be no stopping him.

897
01:15:50,400 --> 01:15:52,640
Thanks for pulling that proposal
together so fast.

898
01:15:53,200 --> 01:15:56,600
- You know, I think I will have that beer.
- You bet.

899
01:16:14,760 --> 01:16:16,720
Harry?

900
01:16:16,880 --> 01:16:18,600
Harry?

901
01:16:20,960 --> 01:16:22,880
Oh, Jesus.

902
01:16:40,080 --> 01:16:41,920
Sure it wasn't the TV, Mrs. Levy?

903
01:16:42,080 --> 01:16:45,960
<i>No, it wasn't the damn TV. I'm telling you,
the guy had a gun in his hand.</i>

904
01:16:46,160 --> 01:16:47,560
Okay, what'd the guy look like?

905
01:16:47,760 --> 01:16:50,440
<i>He was wearing a gray suit with,
like, a necktie.</i>

906
01:17:02,360 --> 01:17:04,000
Shit.

907
01:17:06,440 --> 01:17:08,120
Taxi.

908
01:17:08,680 --> 01:17:11,120
Hey, taxi! Taxi!

909
01:17:30,440 --> 01:17:33,800
Let's go inside and play. Get your toy.

910
01:17:34,120 --> 01:17:35,760
Janet?

911
01:17:36,400 --> 01:17:38,480
Janet...

912
01:17:39,720 --> 01:17:42,320
Janet Stone. She...

913
01:17:42,760 --> 01:17:44,520
- Thank you.
- Over there.

914
01:17:44,720 --> 01:17:45,920
Janet.

915
01:17:46,120 --> 01:17:49,480
- Janet. Janet, let me in, please.
- What are you doing here?

916
01:17:49,640 --> 01:17:52,200
- Get out of here, Jack. You're crazy!
- Let me in.

917
01:17:52,400 --> 01:17:54,480
Get out!

918
01:17:58,480 --> 01:18:01,680
Listen to me. Listen to me. Listen to me.

919
01:18:01,840 --> 01:18:03,560
The man who was in my office.

920
01:18:03,720 --> 01:18:06,440
Mr. Redmond. He's a bank robber.

921
01:18:06,640 --> 01:18:09,920
He's got Beth and the kids.
He's gonna kill them.

922
01:18:10,080 --> 01:18:12,080
They may be dead already.
I need your help.

923
01:18:12,280 --> 01:18:16,480
Do you understand me?
I need your help to try and save them.

924
01:18:17,320 --> 01:18:18,760
Okay.

925
01:18:19,200 --> 01:18:21,880
- I understand.
- Don't scream.

926
01:18:29,200 --> 01:18:31,520
- Sorry.
- Shouldn't we call the police?

927
01:18:35,000 --> 01:18:37,000
No. No police.

928
01:18:37,640 --> 01:18:38,920
What about Harry?

929
01:18:41,600 --> 01:18:42,840
Harry's dead.

930
01:18:43,760 --> 01:18:45,920
Jesus.

931
01:18:48,640 --> 01:18:51,120
I was at Harry's apartment when Cox...

932
01:18:51,320 --> 01:18:53,960
...or Redmond, whatever his name is,
shot him.

933
01:18:54,160 --> 01:18:56,640
People there saw me
with a gun in my hand.

934
01:18:56,800 --> 01:18:59,520
There's a dead man in my house.

935
01:18:59,680 --> 01:19:01,440
By the time I explain to the police...

936
01:19:03,080 --> 01:19:05,840
- ... Beth and the kids could be dead.
- God.

937
01:19:06,040 --> 01:19:07,880
I need you to help me find Bobby.

938
01:19:08,040 --> 01:19:10,040
- Bobby? Why?
- I need his cell phone.

939
01:19:10,200 --> 01:19:13,080
I used his phone to photograph
some account code numbers.

940
01:19:13,280 --> 01:19:16,320
I've gotta have it to get the money back.
Can you help me?

941
01:19:16,480 --> 01:19:19,040
Yeah. I'll find his number.

942
01:19:38,360 --> 01:19:41,720
Why can't you get
a rare burger anymore?

943
01:19:41,880 --> 01:19:43,960
E. Coli.

944
01:19:46,440 --> 01:19:49,240
- Everything all right?
- Yeah. Did you talk to Liam?

945
01:19:49,400 --> 01:19:53,080
- No, not yet.
- Where the hell is he, man?

946
01:19:53,440 --> 01:19:55,160
- Let's go.
- Now?

947
01:19:55,320 --> 01:19:57,120
Yeah, now!

948
01:19:58,720 --> 01:20:00,000
Shit.

949
01:20:00,720 --> 01:20:03,160
You guys need to go to the washroom?

950
01:20:03,760 --> 01:20:05,960
Don't say I didn't ask.

951
01:20:14,920 --> 01:20:16,480
Jack.

952
01:20:16,840 --> 01:20:18,800
- Jesus.
- I found Bobby.

953
01:20:18,960 --> 01:20:21,080
Oh, great.

954
01:20:24,440 --> 01:20:27,600
- It's Cox.
- Are you gonna answer?

955
01:20:28,840 --> 01:20:33,600
I'm not ready to talk to him yet.
I need Bobby's cell phone first.

956
01:20:33,920 --> 01:20:36,920
- And I'll need your laptop.
- No problem.

957
01:20:37,080 --> 01:20:40,760
- And can we use your car?
- Problem.

958
01:20:41,640 --> 01:20:43,880
Pop it! Pop it! Pop the clutch!

959
01:20:45,360 --> 01:20:47,840
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

960
01:20:50,600 --> 01:20:51,840
Keep the gas up.

961
01:21:06,560 --> 01:21:09,320
I can't believe Harry's dead.

962
01:21:11,000 --> 01:21:12,960
Was he involved with Cox?

963
01:21:13,160 --> 01:21:14,920
No.

964
01:21:17,640 --> 01:21:20,680
No. Harry thought he was a businessman.

965
01:21:21,200 --> 01:21:24,360
But didn't Harry introduce you to Cox?

966
01:21:24,520 --> 01:21:26,360
The whole...

967
01:21:27,280 --> 01:21:30,040
...investment thing was just a scam.

968
01:21:30,920 --> 01:21:34,880
Cox was using Harry to get next to me.
Harry didn't know about the robbery.

969
01:21:35,960 --> 01:21:37,880
Cox killed him with my gun...

970
01:21:38,040 --> 01:21:42,800
...to make it look as if I shot him
in a jealous rage over Beth.

971
01:21:42,960 --> 01:21:45,760
Harry and Beth? Give me a break.

972
01:21:45,960 --> 01:21:51,840
He planted a message from Beth
on Harry's answering machine.

973
01:21:54,640 --> 01:21:56,840
Saying she...

974
01:21:59,640 --> 01:22:02,800
Saying she was leaving me.

975
01:22:03,080 --> 01:22:08,400
I also found some encrypted files
on his computer.

976
01:22:08,560 --> 01:22:12,560
I'm sure they'd tie him and me
together in the robbery.

977
01:22:12,760 --> 01:22:15,280
Cox had it all planned out.

978
01:22:15,440 --> 01:22:17,000
Even the gambling debts.

979
01:22:18,480 --> 01:22:20,440
We hatch this plan to rob the bank...

980
01:22:20,600 --> 01:22:22,920
...then I find out my buddy is
sleeping with my wife.

981
01:22:23,400 --> 01:22:27,080
After the robbery, I go to his apartment,
I kill him and I...

982
01:22:28,360 --> 01:22:31,120
I disappear with the money forever.

983
01:22:32,600 --> 01:22:35,080
Forever, as in dead?

984
01:22:38,360 --> 01:22:41,440
I killed the man who was
supposed to kill me.

985
01:22:59,640 --> 01:23:01,760
Be right back.

986
01:23:24,880 --> 01:23:28,000
- What are you doing?
- I didn't tell Jack any of that stuff.

987
01:23:28,200 --> 01:23:31,880
- Why did he say you did?
- I don't know. I'm sorry about that.

988
01:23:32,040 --> 01:23:33,560
Can I borrow your cell phone?

989
01:23:33,760 --> 01:23:37,000
Your cell phone, do you have it?
Can I borrow it?

990
01:23:37,840 --> 01:23:39,400
Thanks.

991
01:23:43,920 --> 01:23:45,920
- Here.
- Great.

992
01:23:46,120 --> 01:23:47,600
Please let this work.

993
01:23:58,960 --> 01:24:01,560
- Here we go.
- Now what?

994
01:24:01,720 --> 01:24:04,160
I just need to find
a wire-transfer terminal.

995
01:24:04,320 --> 01:24:07,480
Where are you gonna find
a bank open at this hour?

996
01:24:09,920 --> 01:24:13,760
<i>Welcome to Seattle-Tacoma
International Airport.</i>

997
01:24:18,880 --> 01:24:21,640
Jack, you look like a bank robber.

998
01:24:23,640 --> 01:24:26,000
- Keep the motor running.
- Good luck.

999
01:24:26,720 --> 01:24:28,400
Thank you.

1000
01:24:55,560 --> 01:24:57,560
We'll see you in the morning.

1001
01:25:00,760 --> 01:25:03,080
I'm sorry, we're closed.

1002
01:25:10,480 --> 01:25:13,280
I need to get on your
wire-transfer terminal.

1003
01:25:13,440 --> 01:25:14,960
Absolutely. I'm sorry.

1004
01:25:15,160 --> 01:25:18,360
We usually don't have
a supervisor here this late.

1005
01:25:18,520 --> 01:25:20,080
- You can use this one.
- Thank you.

1006
01:25:22,120 --> 01:25:23,680
The money is put away. I...

1007
01:25:23,880 --> 01:25:26,440
It's not about the money.
Sit down. Sit down.

1008
01:25:27,800 --> 01:25:29,240
I'm not gonna hurt you.

1009
01:25:30,440 --> 01:25:35,480
8499116...

1010
01:25:56,880 --> 01:25:58,280
Liam, where have you been?

1011
01:25:58,480 --> 01:26:00,280
Change of plans, asshole.

1012
01:26:02,240 --> 01:26:04,480
Jack. Where are you?

1013
01:26:04,640 --> 01:26:08,960
At a bank. I just hacked
into your Cayman Island accounts.

1014
01:26:09,160 --> 01:26:11,200
<i>- That's impossible.
- You think so?</i>

1015
01:26:11,360 --> 01:26:15,240
<i>I have your account details.
You just lost 20 million.</i>

1016
01:26:15,400 --> 01:26:17,360
Bullshit.

1017
01:26:26,760 --> 01:26:28,120
What's going on?

1018
01:26:28,280 --> 01:26:29,560
Check the accounts.

1019
01:26:29,720 --> 01:26:32,560
- What for?
- Can you check the accounts, please?

1020
01:26:32,960 --> 01:26:34,800
Yeah.

1021
01:26:41,480 --> 01:26:43,040
There goes another 20 million.

1022
01:26:43,880 --> 01:26:45,600
- Come on.
- I'm going as fast as I can.

1023
01:26:47,280 --> 01:26:49,880
We're down 40 million.

1024
01:26:50,080 --> 01:26:53,440
Now you know what it feels like
to lose what you love.

1025
01:26:54,600 --> 01:26:57,120
- Another account just cleared.
- That was for Harry.

1026
01:26:57,320 --> 01:26:59,800
Your family are dead. Do you hear me?
They are dead!

1027
01:27:00,000 --> 01:27:02,000
For all I know, they're dead already.

1028
01:27:02,880 --> 01:27:04,320
He emptied another one.

1029
01:27:04,480 --> 01:27:06,360
You're down to your last 20 million.

1030
01:27:12,720 --> 01:27:15,160
- Talk to your husband.
- Jack?

1031
01:27:15,800 --> 01:27:20,000
<i>I love you. Just do whatever you can
to save the children.</i>

1032
01:27:20,200 --> 01:27:23,760
I am, baby. I love you too.

1033
01:27:26,280 --> 01:27:29,360
Put the money back
or I'll put a bullet through her head.

1034
01:27:29,520 --> 01:27:32,120
You do anything to her or my children...

1035
01:27:32,280 --> 01:27:34,200
<i>...and you don't get a dime.</i>

1036
01:27:34,360 --> 01:27:35,600
It's all gone.

1037
01:27:36,080 --> 01:27:38,480
Jack, calm down.
If you calm down, we can talk this...

1038
01:27:38,680 --> 01:27:41,000
You'll get the money
when I get my family.

1039
01:27:41,160 --> 01:27:44,040
Tomorrow morning, when the banks open.
I'll let you know where.

1040
01:27:44,520 --> 01:27:46,960
<i>- Yeah, I'll be there.
- Do you hear me?</i>

1041
01:27:47,160 --> 01:27:49,400
<i>- I'll be there. Just...
- Don't bother calling me.</i>

1042
01:27:49,760 --> 01:27:52,560
Because I've got nothing to say to you.

1043
01:27:54,640 --> 01:27:56,720
- You need to get out of here.
- What?

1044
01:27:56,880 --> 01:27:58,800
- I pushed the silent alarm.
- When?

1045
01:27:58,960 --> 01:28:02,200
A couple of minutes ago. I'm sorry.

1046
01:28:02,840 --> 01:28:04,600
Liam was gonna take care of him.

1047
01:28:04,760 --> 01:28:06,200
Put the woman back in the van.

1048
01:28:06,360 --> 01:28:10,360
- How you gonna give me my money?!
- Put her back in the van!

1049
01:28:13,800 --> 01:28:15,280
Shut up!

1050
01:28:19,680 --> 01:28:21,440
Shit.

1051
01:28:31,280 --> 01:28:33,160
- Move it!
- Just a second. Here he is.

1052
01:28:33,320 --> 01:28:35,800
- Get out of here, now.
- Sorry.

1053
01:28:37,080 --> 01:28:38,720
What happened?

1054
01:28:39,240 --> 01:28:41,040
They're alive.

1055
01:28:41,240 --> 01:28:42,440
Thank God.

1056
01:28:42,640 --> 01:28:45,120
I just bet everything on Cox's greed.

1057
01:28:45,280 --> 01:28:47,040
I got the money.

1058
01:28:47,200 --> 01:28:49,520
So we still got a chance.

1059
01:28:50,320 --> 01:28:51,640
What are you gonna do?

1060
01:28:51,800 --> 01:28:54,680
I'm gonna meet Cox at the bank
in the morning.

1061
01:28:55,320 --> 01:28:57,600
- How are you gonna get in?
- I can't. You can.

1062
01:28:57,760 --> 01:28:59,800
You fired me, remember?
I don't have a pass.

1063
01:29:04,720 --> 01:29:07,320
Barking. Jesus, he was barking.

1064
01:29:07,480 --> 01:29:08,760
- Jack?
- He was...

1065
01:29:08,920 --> 01:29:10,640
Pull over. Pull over here.

1066
01:29:19,960 --> 01:29:22,000
Jack, what are you doing?

1067
01:29:23,360 --> 01:29:25,320
I heard Rusty barking.

1068
01:29:25,520 --> 01:29:28,480
- He's with Beth and the kids in the van.
- So?

1069
01:29:28,640 --> 01:29:30,400
He's got this...

1070
01:29:30,800 --> 01:29:33,960
...GPS. He's got this GPS thing.

1071
01:29:34,160 --> 01:29:35,960
You're not making any sense.

1072
01:29:36,120 --> 01:29:38,200
He was running away all the time...

1073
01:29:38,400 --> 01:29:40,560
...so we got him a collar
with a GPS locator.

1074
01:29:40,720 --> 01:29:43,600
It's from this website.
If he's still got it on...

1075
01:29:47,480 --> 01:29:49,880
Got him. There they are.

1076
01:29:53,360 --> 01:29:54,720
What are they doing?

1077
01:29:54,920 --> 01:29:56,200
Driving out of town.

1078
01:29:56,360 --> 01:29:59,520
Why is he doing that?
Didn't he say he would meet you here?

1079
01:30:00,680 --> 01:30:03,160
- Here. Get in the car.
- What are you doing?

1080
01:30:04,160 --> 01:30:06,120
I'm gonna find my dog.

1081
01:30:20,760 --> 01:30:23,400
Can you shut the dog up?

1082
01:30:23,560 --> 01:30:25,080
It's okay, Rusty.

1083
01:30:27,520 --> 01:30:29,760
You know, you're never
gonna get that money now.

1084
01:30:30,840 --> 01:30:35,240
But if you turn around and take us back, my
husband can give you whatever you want.

1085
01:30:35,400 --> 01:30:39,280
- You can split it between the two of you.
- Shut the damn dog up!

1086
01:30:59,640 --> 01:31:01,280
Jack.

1087
01:31:02,880 --> 01:31:04,840
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay. Yeah.

1088
01:31:05,000 --> 01:31:06,920
- You want me to drive?
- No. No, I'm fine.

1089
01:31:08,240 --> 01:31:09,520
Where are they now?

1090
01:31:10,760 --> 01:31:12,000
They're still on the 2.

1091
01:31:39,320 --> 01:31:41,120
They just turned off the road.

1092
01:31:41,320 --> 01:31:45,000
There's nothing on this map
except a big lake and some railroad tracks.

1093
01:31:45,160 --> 01:31:47,440
- How far?
- Twenty miles.

1094
01:31:47,600 --> 01:31:50,240
Where the hell are they going?

1095
01:31:53,640 --> 01:31:55,600
Shut up.

1096
01:31:56,200 --> 01:31:59,160
Shut your goddamn dog up.
I swear to God.

1097
01:31:59,320 --> 01:32:00,920
It's okay, Rusty.

1098
01:32:01,080 --> 01:32:03,160
- Come here, Rusty. Come here.
- Shut up!

1099
01:32:05,840 --> 01:32:07,680
That's it!

1100
01:32:08,400 --> 01:32:10,160
I warned you!

1101
01:32:11,640 --> 01:32:14,200
What are you doing? No! Rusty!

1102
01:32:14,440 --> 01:32:17,080
Shut up or you're going next!

1103
01:32:18,240 --> 01:32:20,720
- Rusty! Sorry, baby.
- Quiet!

1104
01:32:20,920 --> 01:32:22,840
You hear me?

1105
01:32:53,880 --> 01:32:55,120
Put them in the back room.

1106
01:32:55,280 --> 01:32:57,880
Maybe we should just forget it.

1107
01:32:58,040 --> 01:32:59,560
Let them all go.

1108
01:32:59,760 --> 01:33:04,000
Maybe you should do your job
and put them in the back room.

1109
01:33:16,040 --> 01:33:18,080
Why would he bring them
all the way out here?

1110
01:33:19,120 --> 01:33:23,960
I don't think he was planning
on leaving anyone alive.

1111
01:33:27,200 --> 01:33:28,960
God.

1112
01:33:37,280 --> 01:33:38,640
- Hey.
- Oh, my God. Come here.

1113
01:33:38,840 --> 01:33:40,080
- It's all right.
- Hey.

1114
01:33:40,280 --> 01:33:43,200
- He can't breathe.
- Sit your ass down. I don't give a rat's ass.

1115
01:33:43,360 --> 01:33:46,760
- I'm sick of you people, man.
- Honey.

1116
01:33:47,240 --> 01:33:49,000
Vel.

1117
01:33:49,720 --> 01:33:51,920
Please help us.

1118
01:34:01,920 --> 01:34:04,080
We need to exchange you...

1119
01:34:04,240 --> 01:34:08,200
...for the money,
and then we'll let you go.

1120
01:34:09,440 --> 01:34:10,920
Okay?

1121
01:34:12,440 --> 01:34:14,320
You'll be all right.

1122
01:34:14,480 --> 01:34:15,760
Thank you.

1123
01:34:25,120 --> 01:34:26,480
They're slowing down.

1124
01:34:29,320 --> 01:34:31,160
Look.

1125
01:34:38,440 --> 01:34:40,040
Rusty.

1126
01:34:40,680 --> 01:34:41,960
Rusty.

1127
01:34:42,120 --> 01:34:45,000
Come here, Rusty. It's okay.

1128
01:34:45,840 --> 01:34:48,200
Where are they, Rusty?

1129
01:34:49,280 --> 01:34:50,600
Where have they gone?

1130
01:34:50,760 --> 01:34:52,920
Where's Andy?

1131
01:34:57,480 --> 01:35:00,400
There's a house down there by the lake.
I see Beth's car.

1132
01:35:00,560 --> 01:35:02,080
- You got a cell phone?
- Yeah.

1133
01:35:02,280 --> 01:35:03,520
Call the police.

1134
01:35:03,720 --> 01:35:06,160
Shouldn't we just wait here
for the police?

1135
01:35:07,080 --> 01:35:08,720
No.

1136
01:35:08,880 --> 01:35:10,600
I can't. I can't wait.

1137
01:35:10,800 --> 01:35:12,240
Thanks for everything.

1138
01:35:12,400 --> 01:35:14,480
You got your job back.

1139
01:35:56,520 --> 01:35:58,240
Will he call?

1140
01:35:58,920 --> 01:36:01,200
You think he'll just give us the money,
no police?

1141
01:36:02,240 --> 01:36:05,280
He knows I'll kill his family if he doesn't.

1142
01:36:08,400 --> 01:36:11,520
I just need to up the ante a little.

1143
01:36:16,800 --> 01:36:19,120
No. Please don't.
What are you doing?

1144
01:36:19,280 --> 01:36:21,080
- Let her go!
- No!

1145
01:36:21,240 --> 01:36:22,800
Stop it!

1146
01:36:23,640 --> 01:36:24,920
- My God!
- Oh, my God!

1147
01:36:25,080 --> 01:36:26,480
- Come on.
- Shut up!

1148
01:36:26,680 --> 01:36:29,080
Why are you doing this?

1149
01:36:29,320 --> 01:36:30,560
Pim!

1150
01:36:38,680 --> 01:36:40,320
Come here!

1151
01:36:53,400 --> 01:36:56,200
Where you at, sweetie? Wanna play?

1152
01:36:56,360 --> 01:36:58,600
Marco.

1153
01:36:58,800 --> 01:37:00,480
Polo.

1154
01:37:03,680 --> 01:37:05,560
Marco.

1155
01:37:05,720 --> 01:37:08,200
Polo.

1156
01:37:18,760 --> 01:37:20,160
Hey!

1157
01:37:34,200 --> 01:37:35,840
- Help! We're in here!
- Come on!

1158
01:37:42,440 --> 01:37:43,680
Dad!

1159
01:37:44,560 --> 01:37:46,920
- Dad!
- Run, Sarah. Run and hide!

1160
01:37:48,120 --> 01:37:49,920
- Move it!
- Dad!

1161
01:37:50,080 --> 01:37:52,560
Put him down. Let him go! Oh, my...

1162
01:37:57,320 --> 01:37:59,800
Get upstairs now!

1163
01:38:06,080 --> 01:38:08,200
Come on, get up the stairs!

1164
01:38:08,360 --> 01:38:11,680
- Move it! Move it!
- Let me go!

1165
01:38:13,360 --> 01:38:15,720
Go on, now. Move it! Get up there!

1166
01:38:27,560 --> 01:38:28,960
Daddy!

1167
01:38:31,200 --> 01:38:33,160
Daddy!

1168
01:39:22,800 --> 01:39:24,280
- Jack!
- Run, Beth! Run!

1169
01:39:24,720 --> 01:39:26,160
Run.

1170
01:40:35,840 --> 01:40:37,320
Beth.

1171
01:40:37,680 --> 01:40:38,920
Beth!

1172
01:40:40,360 --> 01:40:41,640
Jack?

1173
01:40:41,800 --> 01:40:43,800
Beth!

1174
01:40:46,680 --> 01:40:48,400
Jack!

